    S:gt.blockmachines.bw.biovat.tooltip=Machine Type: §eBacterial Vat, Bac Vat§r\n§bAdvanced Bio Processing\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nSome recipes require §aR§2A§aD§2I§aA§2T§aI§2O§aN§7 supplied with a §l§aRadio Hatch\nRadiation can be either a minimum requirement or an exact value\nEfficiency depends on Output Hatch fluid level\nEfficiency peaks at §d50%\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.bw.biovat.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§64§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   19x §r§7Clean Stainless Steel Casings (minimum)\n§f   Glass: §7Hollow two middle layers\n§6   32x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (tiered)\n   Some Recipes need more advanced Glass Types\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Radio Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any casing\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.bw.manualtrafo.name=변압기 설명서
    S:gt.blockmachines.bw.manualtrafo.tooltip=Machine Type: §eTransformer§r\nOperates in 4 diffrent modes:\nMode 1: Circuit 0 in controller: Direct-Upstep\nMode 2: Circuit 1 in controller: Direct-Downstep\nMode 3: Circuit 2 in controller: Tapped-Upstep (currently disabled)\nMode 4: Circuit 2 in controller: Tapped-Downstep (currently disabled)\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.bw.manualtrafo.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63§7x§63-10§7x§63§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   0x §r§7MV Machine Casing (minimum)\n§f   Transformer-Winding Blocks: §71 Layer for each tier transformed\n§f   Nickel-Zinc-Ferrite Blocks: §7Middle of Transformer-Winding Blocks\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any bottom layer casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any bottom layer casing\n§f   Dynamo Hatch: §7Any top layer casing\n   \n   Tapped Mode :\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Touching Transformer-Winding Blocks\n§f   Dynamo Hatch: §7Touching Transformer-Winding Blocks\n   Hatches touching Transformer-Winding Blocks must be tiered from bottom to top\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
