    S:gt.blockmachines.circuitassemblyline.tooltip=Machine Type: §eCircuit Assembler, CAL§r\nChange Mode with Screwdriver\n§bMachine does not lose efficiency when overclocked\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§6Circuit Assembly Line Mode:\nImprint this machine with a Circuit Imprint,\nby putting the imprint in the controller\nEvery Circuit Assembly Line can only be imprinted ONCE\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§6Circuit Assembler Mode:\nDoes Circuit Assembler recipes, Minimum Length: §c5§7\nRecipe tier in Circuit Assembler mode is at most Energy Hatch tier - 1\nThis mode supports Crafting Input Buffer/Bus and allows bus separation\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.circuitassemblyline.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §62-7§7x§63§7x§63§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   From Bottom to Top, Left to Right\n   Layer 1 - Solid Steel Machine Casing, Input bus (Last Output bus), Solid Steel Machine Casing\n   Layer 2 - §8EV§r+ Tier Glass, Assembly Line Casing, §8EV§r+ Tier Glass\n   Layer 3 - Grate Machine Casing\n   Up to 7 repeating slices, last is Output Bus\n   §fController: §7Layer 3 first slice front\n§f   1x Energy Hatch: §7Any layer 3 casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any layer 1 casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7As specified on layer 1\n§f   Output Bus: §7As specified in final slice on layer 1\n§f   §8EV§r+ Tier Glass: §7As specified on layer 2\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any layer 1 casing\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
