    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beam-mirror.name=Beam Mirror
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beam-mirror.tooltip=Machine Type: §eBeam Mirror§r\nTakes in particle beams and sends them back out\n§6That's literally it.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §aAuthor: §6Ham§fCorp§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beam-mirror.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63§7x§65§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   40x §r§7Collider Casing\n§6   5x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (tiered)\n§6   1x §r§7Beamline Input Hatch\n§6   1x §r§7Beamline Output Hatch\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beam-splitter.name=Beam Splitter
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beam-splitter.tooltip=Machine Type: §eBeam Splitter§r\nSelect which particles to blacklist in the output hatches\nInput particles will be split evenly among all valid output hatches\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §aAuthor: §6Ham§fCorp§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beam-splitter.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §69§7x§63§7x§69§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   68x §r§7Collider Casing\n§6   9x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (tiered)\n§6   1x §r§7Beamline Input Hatch\n§6   4x §r§7Filtered Beamline Output Hatch\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beam-stabilizer.name=Beam Stabilizer
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beam-stabilizer.tooltip=Machine Type: §eBeam Stabilizer§r\nAccepts and stores up to 100000 §aParticles§7 from\npotentially intermittent high §cRate§7 particle beam packets\nand re-releases those particles as a stable beam at a\n§cRate§7 of your choosing\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nIf a particle beam with a different §aParticle§7, §6Energy§7 or\n§bFocus§7 is sent to the machine during operation, it is\nignored UNLESS there are no currently stored §aParticles\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §aAuthor: §6Ham§fCorp§r§7 & §aAuthor: §5§ozub§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.beam-stabilizer.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §67§7x§67§7x§611§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   109x §r§7Collider Casing\n§6   9x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (tiered)\n§6   1x §r§7Beamline Input Hatch\n§6   1x §r§7Beamline Output Hatch\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.blackholecompressor.name=준안정 블랙홀 격리장
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.blackholecompressor.tooltip=Machine Type: §eCompressor, Advanced Neutronium Compressor, BHC§r\n§dUses the immense power of the event horizon to compress things\n§dNo longer requires heat management to perform superdense compression\n§dCan create advanced singularities!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nInsert a §fBlack Hole Seed§7 to open a black hole\nThe black hole will begin its life at §c100§7 stability and slowly decay\nStability decays by §c1/s§7 until it reaches 0\nAt 0 stability, the black hole is §4UNSTABLE\nOnce the black hole becomes unstable, it will void recipes and eventually close itself!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nThe decay can be §lhalted§r§7 by inserting 1 L/s of spacetime into specific hatches\nEvery §c30§7 total seconds saved by spacetime insertion will §cdouble§7 the cost per second!\nInsert a §fBlack Hole Collapser§7 to close the black hole\nTo restore stability and reset spacetime costs, close the black hole and open a new one\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§fUse circuit 20 for Compressor and 21 for Neutronium Compressor\n§68§7 Parallels per §fVoltage§7 Tier\n§a500%§7 Speed\n§b70%§7 EU Usage\n§c2x/4x§7 parallels when stability is BELOW §c50/20\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§cRecipe tier is limited to hatch tier + 1. Will not perform overclocks above the hatch tier\n§cLimited to one energy hatch if using a Multi-Amp or Laser hatch\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§a§lOllie§r§7 & §aBucketBrigade§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.blackholecompressor.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §635§7x§633§7x§635§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n§6   950x §r§7Background Radiation Absorbent Casing (minimum)\n§6   3667x §r§7Extreme Density Space-Bending Casing\n§6   64x §r§7Hawking Radiation Realignment Focus\n§6   144x §r§7Naquadah Alloy Frame Box\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Spacetime Insertion, Behind Laser\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Radiation Absorbent Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Radiation Absorbent Casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any Radiation Absorbent Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Radiation Absorbent Casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.blastfurnace.name=전기 용광로
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.blastfurnace.tooltip=Machine Type: §eBlast Furnace, EBF§r\nYou can use some fluids to reduce recipe time. Place the circuit in the Input Bus\nIncreases Heat by §c100K§7 for every §fVoltage§7 tier past §bMV\nReduces §bEU Usage§7 by §f5%§7 every §c900K§7 above the recipe requirement\nEvery §c1800K§7 over the recipe requirement grants 1 §dPerfect Overclock\nThat means the EBF will reduce recipe time by a factor 4 instead of 2 (giving 100% efficiency)\n§5400 §7Pollution per second\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
