    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.oreprocessor.name=통합 광석 공장
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.oreprocessor.tooltip=Machine Type: §eOre Processor, IOF§r\n§4DEPRECATED - Controller will be removed in next major update!\n§4Check NEI for new Controller and conversion recipe\nDoes all ore processing in one step\n§61024§7 Parallels\nEvery ore costs 30EU/t, 2L lubricant, 200L distilled water\nRecipes that need extra input require their extra inputs on top of the normal costs\nProcessing time is dependent on mode\nUse a screwdriver to switch mode\nSneak click with screwdriver to void the stone dust\n§5200 §7Pollution per second\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§aOP stands for Ore Processor ;)\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.oreprocessor.tooltip.15564=Machine Type: §eOre Processor, IOF§r\nDoes all ore processing in one step\nParallel count scales with total input power: EU/t / 30\nEvery ore costs 30EU/t, 2L lubricant, 200L distilled water\nRecipes that need extra input require their extra inputs on top of the normal costs\nProcessing time is dependent on mode\nUse a screwdriver to switch mode\nSneak click with screwdriver to void the stone dust\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§5200 §7Pollution per second\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§aOP stands for Ore Processor ;)\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nStructure by: §a§6Bavib§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.oreprocessor.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §66§7x§612§7x§611§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7The third layer\n§6   128x §r§7Advanced Iridium Plated Machine Casing\n§6   105x §r§7Clean Stainless Steel Machine Casing\n§6   48x §r§7Any Tiered Glass\n§6   30x §r§7Tungstensteel Pipe Casing\n§6   16x §r§7Tungstensteel Frame Box\n§6   16x §r§7Steel Gear Box Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any bottom Casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any bottom Casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7Input ore/crushed ore\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Input lubricant/distilled water/washing chemicals\n§f   Muffler Hatch: §7Output Pollution\n§f   Output Bus: §7Output products\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.oreprocessor.tooltip_secondary.15564=§fDimensions: §615§7x§69§7x§613§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   7x §r§7Awakened Draconium Coil Block\n§6   7x §r§7Centrifuge Casing\n§6   7x §r§7Grate Machine Casing\n§6   7x §r§7Large Sieve Grate\n§6   7x §r§7Titanium Gear Box Casing\n§6   90x §r§7Any Tiered Glass\n§6   23x §r§7Stainless Steel Frame Box\n§6   169x §r§7Clean Stainless Steel Machine Casing\n§6   96x §r§7Iridium Sheetmetal\n§6   462x §r§7Advanced Iridium Plated Machine Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any bottom Casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any bottom Casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7Input ore/crushed ore\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Input lubricant/distilled water/washing chemicals\n§f   Muffler Hatch: §7Output Pollution\n§f   Output Bus: §7Output products\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.pcbbiochamber.name=Bio Chamber
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.pcbbiochamber.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePCB Factory Upgrade§r\n§7It enables nanites to construct organic circuitry.\n§7Required for Bioware and Wetware boards.\n§7Place the controller block within §c16§7 blocks of the PCB Factory\n§7Left click the PCB Factory controller with a data stick,\n§7then right click this controller to link.\n§7Can connect to many PCB Factories!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§9§lBlue§b§lWeabo§r§7 & §a§f§lgu§b§lid§3§l118§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.pcbbiochamber.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§67§7x§612§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   68x §r§7Clean Stainless Steel Machine Casing\n§6   40x §r§7Damascus Steel Frame Box\n§6   72x §r§7Any Tiered Glass\n   §7Does not require maintenance or power.\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.pcbcoolingtower.name=Cooling Tower
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.pcbcoolingtower.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePCB Factory Upgrade§r\nThe Cooling Tower enables overclocking of the PCB Factory\nTier 1 gives a normal overclock\nTier 2 gives a §6perfect§7 overclock\nIt requires 10L/s of cooling fluid per active and connected PCB Factory\nTier 1 Cooling Fluid is: §6Distilled Water\nTier 2 Cooling Fluid is: §6Super Coolant\n§7Place the controller block within §c16§7 blocks of the PCB Factory\n§7Left click the PCB Factory controller with a data stick,\n§7then right click this controller to link.\n§7Can connect to many PCB Factories!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§9§lBlue§b§lWeabo§r§7 & §a§f§lgu§b§lid§3§l118§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.pcbcoolingtower.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§610§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   Tier 1\n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   19x §r§7Reinforced Photolithographic Framework Casing\n§6   20x §r§7Tungstensteel Pipe Casing\n§6   40x §r§7Damascus Steel Frame Box\n§6   68x §r§7Radiant Naquadah Alloy Casing\n§6   12x §r§7Extreme Engine Intake Casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Coolant Hatch\n   Tier 2\n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   39x §r§7Reinforced Photolithographic Framework Casing\n§6   40x §r§7Americium Steel Frame Box\n§6   20x §r§7Tungstensteel Pipe Casing\n§6   48x §r§7Infinity Cooled Casing\n§6   8x §r§7Superconducting Coil Block\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Coolant Hatch\n   §7§m------------------------------\n   §7Does not require maintenance or power.\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.pcbfactory.name= PCB 팩토리
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.pcbfactory.tooltip=Machine Type: §eCircuit Board Fabricator§r\nTier of the machine determines the available recipes\nEach tier and upgrade requires additional structures\nPower consumption is multiplied by Sqrt(structures)\nTier 2 and 3 allow parallel by using extra nanites\nNanites have to be placed in a Nanite Containment Bus\nThe formula for parallels is the §6amount of nanites^0.75§7, rounded up\nMaximum parallel is §6256§7\nRecipes require a cooling upgrade to be overclocked\nLiquid Cooling uses §910 L/s§7 of §9distilled water§7 and enables default overclocks\nThermosink uses §b10 L/s§7 of §bSuper Coolant§7 and enables §dperfect overclocks\nTrace size can be changed to modify the material usage and machine speed\nConfigure Trace Size in UI\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§9§lBlue§b§lWeabo§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.pcbfactory.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §630§7x§638§7x§613§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7§61\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7§61§7-§62§7 or §61§7 TT energy hatch\n§f   Input Bus: §7§60§7+\n§f   Output Bus: §7§60§7+\n§f   Input Hatch: §7§60§7+\n   §fNanite Containment Bus: §60§7+\n   §fCoolant Hatch (Input Hatch): §61§7 Center of the Liquid Cooling/Thermosink\n   §9Base Multi (Tier §51§9):\n   §640§7 Damascus Steel Frame Box\n   §69§7 Vibrant Alloy Frame Box\n   §625§7 Any Tiered Glass\n   §677§7 Basic Photolithography Framework Casing\n   §612§7 Grate Machine Casing\n   §625§7 Plascrete Block\n   §9Tier §52§9 (Adds to Tier §51§9):\n   §634§7 Duranium Frame Box\n   §6158§7 Reinforced Photolithography Framework Casing\n   §9Tier §53§9:\n   §6292§7 Radiation Proof Photolithography Framework Casing\n   §676§7 Radiant Naquadah Alloy Casing\n   §9Biochamber Upgrade\n   §668§7 Clean Stainless Steel Machine Casing\n   §640§7 Damascus Steel Frame Box\n   §672§7 Any Tiered Glass\n   §9Liquid Cooling Tower (Tier §51§9):\n   §640§7 Damascus Steel Frame Box\n   §668§7 Radiant Naquadah Alloy Casing\n   §612§7 Extreme Engine Intake Casing\n   §620§7 Tungstensteel Pipe Casing\n   §621§7 Reinforced Photolithography Framework Casing\n   §9Thermosink Radiator(Tier §52§9):\n   §640§7 Americium Frame Box\n   §641§7 Reinforced Photolithography Framework Casing\n   §68§7 Superconducting Coil Block\n   §620§7 Tungstensteel Pipe Casing\n   §648§7 Infinity Cooled Casing\n   \n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.plasmaforge.name=차원을 초월한 플라스마 포지
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.plasmaforge.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePlasma Forge, DTPF§r\nTranscending Dimensional Boundaries.\nTakes §c8§7 hours of continuous run time to fully breach dimensional\nboundaries and achieve maximum efficiency, reducing fuel consumption by up to §c50%\nWhen no recipe is running, fuel discount decays x§c100§7 as fast as it builds up, draining\nthe total amount of stored runtime\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nMultidimensional spaces can be perfectly aligned and synchronized in this state, \nallowing §6Dimensional Convergence §7to occur. To reach the required stability threshold,\na §bTransdimensional Alignment Matrix §7must be placed in the controller\nWhen §6Convergence §7is active, it allows the forge to perform §cPerfect Overclocks§7,\nbut the extra power cost is instead added in form of increased catalyst amounts\nThis machine can run recipes regardless of tier, if given enough energy\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§4§l§o§nC§6§l§o§no§a§l§o§nl§3§l§o§ne§5§l§o§nn§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.plasmaforge.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §633§7x§624§7x§633§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Middle of the structure, 3rd layer\n   §62,112§7 Heating coils required\n   §6120§7 Dimensional bridge blocks required.\n   §61,270§7 Dimensional injection casings required\n   §62,121§7 Dimensionally transcendent casings required\n   \n   Requires §61§7-§62§7 energy hatches or §61§7 TT energy hatch\n   Requires §60§7-§67§7 input hatches\n   Requires §60§7-§62§7 output hatches\n   Requires §60§7-§66§7 input buses\n   Requires §60§7-§61§7 output buses\n   \n   Uses sub channel §6coil§r§7 for §6Heating Coils Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationplant.name=정수장
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationplant.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePurification Plant, WPP§r\nMain controller block for the Water Purification Plant\nFreely place §ePurification Units §7within §c32§7 blocks along each axis\nLeft click this controller with a data stick, then right click a purification unit to link\nSupplies power to linked purification units\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nWorks in fixed time processing cycles of §c120§7 seconds\nAll linked units follow this cycle\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nEvery recipe has a base chance of success. Success rate can be boosted\nby using a portion of the target output as a secondary input\n§c10%§7 of output yield will be consumed in exchange for an\nadditive §c15%§7 increase to success\nOn recipe failure, each purification unit has a §c50%§7 chance\nto return water of the same quality as the input or lower\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nEvery purification unit has a configuration window to configure maximum parallel amount\nThis will only scale purified water input, ALL fluid output and power usage. Other catalysts and outputs are unchanged\nToggle debug mode to reduce cycle time to 30s but disable water I/O\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§b§oContaminants and ionized particles in water can cause significant imperfections in delicate\n§b§oprocesses related to the cutting and engraving of silicon wafers and chips. It is crucial that\n§b§othe water is systematically purified through a series of increasingly precise and complex\n§b§opurification processes, and this multiblock is the heart of the operation\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationplant.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §67§7x§69§7x§68§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   56x §r§7Superplasticizer-Treated High Strength Concrete\n§6   71x§7 - §672x §r§7Sterile Water Plant Casing\n§6   77x §r§7Reinforced Sterile Water Plant Casing\n§6   30x §r§7Tungsten Frame Box\n§6   6x §r§7Tinted Industrial Glass\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7§61\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7§61\n   Requires water to be placed in the tank.\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitclarifier.name=정수 처리 장치
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitclarifier.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePurification Unit§r\n§b§lWater Tier: §f1§r\nMust be linked to a Purification Plant using a data stick to work\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nRequires a filter made of Activated Carbon to work\nEvery cycle, has a §c20%§7 chance to destroy the filter\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§b§oThe first step to acquiring purified water is to filter out macroscopic contaminants through the\n§b§ouse of large physical filters. As more contaminants are captured, the efficacy of the filter\n§b§odecreases so continual replacements must be supplied to maintain full function of the Clarifier.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitclarifier.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §611§7x§64§7x§611§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   123x§7 - §6131x §r§7Reinforced Sterile Water Plant Casing\n§6   21x §r§7Filter Machine Casing\n§6   12x §r§7Iridium Frame Box\n§6   12x §r§7Damascus Steel Frame Box\n§6   3x §r§7PTFE Pipe Casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7§61§7+\n§f   Output Bus: §7§61§7+\n§f   Input Hatch: §7§61§7+\n§f   Output Hatch: §7§61§7+\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitdegasifier.name=잔류 오염 제거 장치
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitdegasifier.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePurification Unit§r\n§b§lWater Tier: §f7§r\nMust be linked to a Purification Plant using a data stick to work\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nAt the start of the operation, the §fDegasser Control Hatch§7 will output a redstone signal\nTo succeed the recipe, you will need to successfully decode the instructions in the signal\nTo decode the signal, interpret the signal strength as a 4-bit number from 0-15\nDenote the lowest bit as bit 1, and the highest as bit 4\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§f§lBit 1: §9§lOzone Sparging by Inert Gas\nIf this bit is on, you must insert an §finert gas§7 into the machine\nTo determine which gas to insert, interpret bits §f2-3§7 as a 2-bit number\n§70: §c10000L §fHelium§7 / 1: §c7500L §fNeon§7 / 2: §c5000L §fKrypton§7 / 3: §c2500L §fXenon\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§f§lBit 2: §9§lSuperconductive Deionization\nIf this bit is on, you must insert §c1440L §fMolten Superconductor Base.\nUsing higher tier superconductor provides bonus output\nOutput multiplier: §2UV§7: §f1x§7 / §4UHV§7: §f1.25x§7 / §5UEV§7: §f1.5x§7 / §1§lUIV§7: §f1.75x§7 / §c§lUMV§7: §f2x\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§f§lBit 3: §9§lGravitationally-Generated Differential Vacuum Extraction\nIf this bit is on, you must insert §c4608L §fMolten Neutronium\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§f§lBit 4: §9§lSeldonian Settlement Process\nIf this bit is on,§c DISREGARD §7all other bits and do not insert anything\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§f§lNo bits: §9§lMachine Overload\nIn rare cases, the machine may overload and output no control signal at all\nTo prevent machine damage, insert §c10000L §fSuper Coolant.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nThe recipe can only succeed if the entire signal is decoded correctly\nInserting any fluid not requested by the signal will always void the recipe\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§b§oThe penultimate stage of water purification, step seven, is an irregular series of complex\n§b§oprocesses designed to remove any residual materials left by the decontaminants from the previous\n§b§osteps such as any energetic ions, acids, clarifiers, or gasses. Depending on what the Degasser\n§b§odetects in the water, it will request various materials to complete the processes listed above.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitdegasifier.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §617§7x§625§7x§617§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center, 2nd layer\n§6   780x§7 - §6803x §r§7Heat-Resistant Trinium Plated Casing\n§6   622x §r§7Omni-Purpose Infinity Fused Glass\n§6   124x §r§7Bedrockium Frame Box\n§f   Output Hatch: §7§61§7+, Any Trinium Casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7§61§7+, Any Trinium Casing\n§f   Degasser Control Hatch: §7§61§7, Any Trinium Casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitextractor.name=절대 중입자 완전 정화 장치
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitextractor.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePurification Unit§r\n§b§lWater Tier: §f8§r\nMust be linked to a Purification Plant using a data stick to work\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nInsert §fQuark Releasing Catalysts §7into the input bus while running\nEvery recipe cycle, a different combination of §c2§7 different §fQuark Releasing Catalysts\nwill correctly identify the lone quark and succeed the recipe\nThe order of catalysts in the combination does not matter, so §9Up§7/§dDown§7 can be identified by inserting §dDown§7/§9Up\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nEvery §c20§7 ticks, consumes ALL catalysts in the input bus\nThe base cost of inserting a catalyst is §c144L§f Molten Infinity\nFor every duplicate occurrence of an inserted catalyst in the sequence, this cost is doubled\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nKeeps track of the entire sequence of catalysts inserted this recipe\nIf the correct catalyst combination is in the sequence of inserted catalysts, immediately outputs §c2000L §fStabilised Baryonic Matter\nAt the end of a successful recipe, outputs additional §c500L §fStabilised Baryonic Matter§7 per parallel\nAt the end of the recipe, returns all incorrectly inserted catalysts in the output bus\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§b§oThe final stage of water purification goes beyond subatomic particles and identifies the smallest\n§b§opossible imperfections within the baryons themselves. By correctly identifying which pairs of quark\n§b§oflavors are required, the unit will activate the catalysts, stabilizing the errant particles\n§b§oThis ultimately creates both Stabilised Baryonic Matter and, most importantly, absolutely perfectly purified water.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitextractor.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §617§7x§617§7x§617§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   300x §r§7Quark Exclusion Casing (minimum)\n§6   96x §r§7Femtometer-Calibrated Particle Beam Casing\n§6   37x §r§7Particle Beam Guidance Pipe Casing\n§6   240x §r§7Non-Photonic Matter Exclusion Glass\n§6   108x §r§7Bedrockium Frame Box\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Quark Exclusion Casing. Stocking bus is blacklisted.\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any Quark Exclusion Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Quark Exclusion Casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Any Quark Exclusion Casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitflocculator.name=응집 처리 장치
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitflocculator.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePurification Unit§r\n§b§lWater Tier: §f3§r\nMust be linked to a Purification Plant using a data stick to work\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nSupply with §f%s§7 to operate\nOutputs §f%s§7 that can be recycled\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nDuring operation, will consume ALL §f%s§7 in the input hatch\nAt the end of the recipe, for every §c100000L §7of §f%s§7 consumed\ngain an additive §c10.0%%§7 increase to success. If total fluid supplied is not\na multiple of §c100000L§7, a penalty to success is applied using the following formula:\n§aSuccess = Success * 2^(-10 * Overflow ratio)\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§b§oStep three in purifying water is to remove microscopic contaminants such as dusts, microplastics and other\n§b§opollutants using a clarifying agent (In this case, polyaluminium chloride) to cause flocculation - the process\n§b§oof aggregating dispersed suspended particles from a solution into larger clumps for further filtration.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitflocculator.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §69§7x§65§7x§68§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   56x§7 - §665x §r§7Slick Sterile Flocculation Casing\n§6   30x §r§7Sterile Water Plant Casing\n§6   16x §r§7Reinforced Sterile Water Plant Casing\n§6   6x §r§7Tinted Industrial Glass\n§6   12x §r§7Adamantium Frame Box\n§6   9x §r§7Filter Machine Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7§61§7+\n§f   Input Hatch: §7§61§7-§63\n§f   Output Hatch: §7§61§7-§63\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitozonation.name=오존 정화 장치
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitozonation.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePurification Unit§r\n§b§lWater Tier: §f2§r\nMust be linked to a Purification Plant using a data stick to work\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nWill explode if the input hatch contains more than §c1024000L §fOzone Gas\nReceives a §c20%§7 bonus to success chance for every doubling of §fOzone Gas\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§b§oThe second step in water purification is ozonation, which involves injecting large quantities of small\n§b§obubbles of highly reactive ozone gas into the water. This removes trace element contaminants like\n§b§osulfur, iron and manganese, creating insoluble oxide compounds which are then filtered out.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitozonation.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §69§7x§610§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   96x§7 - §6102x §r§7Inert Filtration Casing\n§6   28x §r§7Reactive Gas Containment Casing\n§6   9x §r§7Any Tinted Industrial Glass\n§6   6x §r§7Tungstensteel Frame Box\n§6   3x §r§7PTFE Pipe Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7§61§7+\n§f   Input Hatch: §7§61§7+\n§f   Output Hatch: §7§61§7+\n§f   Input Hatch (Ozone): §7§61\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitphadjustment.name=pH 중화 및 정화 장치
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitphadjustment.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePurification Unit§r\n§b§lWater Tier: §f4§r\nMust be linked to a Purification Plant using a data stick to work\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nInitial pH value every cycle varies from §c4.5§7 - §c9.5 pH\nIf the pH value is within §c0.05 pH §7of 7.0 pH at the end of the cycle, the recipe always succeeds\nOtherwise, the recipe always fails\nUse a pH Sensor Hatch to read the current pH value\nFor safety, the machine will shut down if the pH goes below 0 or exceeds 14\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nEvery §c20§7 ticks, consumes ALL §f%s§7 and §f%s§7 in the special hatches\n§cRaises §7the pH value by §c0.01 pH §7per piece of §fSodium Hydroxide Dust\n§cLowers §7the pH value by §c0.01 pH §7per §c10L §7of §fHydrochloric Acid\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§b§oThe fourth step of water purification is to neutralize the solution and bring its pH to exactly 7, rendering\n§b§othe solution inert with no hydrogen ion activity beyond water’s natural amphiproticity. Acids and bases from soils\n§b§oand geology cause natural alkalinity variations in water which can cause corrosive reactions with sensitive\n§b§omaterials. This necessitates the use of the corresponding neutralizing agents to pH balance the water.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitphadjustment.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §615§7x§66§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   16x §r§7Stabilized Naquadah Water Plant Casing\n§6   18x §r§7Chemical Grade Glass\n§6   48x §r§7Naquadah Alloy Frame Box\n§6   134x §r§7Inert Neutralization Water Plant Casing\n§f   Input Hatch (Water): §7§61+\n§f   Output Hatch: §7§61\n§f   pH Sensor Hatch: §7§62\n§f   Input Bus (Sodium Hydroxide): §7§61\n§f   Input Hatch (Hydrochloric Acid): §7§61\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitplasmaheater.name=극한 온도 변화 정화 장치
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitplasmaheater.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePurification Unit§r\n§b§lWater Tier: §f5§r\nMust be linked to a Purification Plant using a data stick to work\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nComplete heating cycles by first heating the water to §c10000K§7,\nand then cooling it back down to §c0K\nInitial temperature is reset to §c0K§7 on recipe start\nEach completed heating cycle boosts success chance by §c33%\nIf the temperature ever reaches §c12500K§7 the recipe will fail and output steam\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nConsumes up to §c10L/s §fHelium Plasma§7 and up to §c100L/s §fSuper Coolant\n§cRaises §7the temperature by §c100K§7 per liter of plasma consumed\n§cLowers §7the temperature by §c5K§7 per liter of coolant consumed\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§b§oStep five of water purification is to evaporate complex organic polymers and extremophile organisms\n§b§othat might be resistant to simple acids, clarifying agents, and filters. Using an ultra high\n§b§opressure chamber in combination with extreme temperature fluctuations allows the water to remain\n§b§osupercritical while evaporating any remaining contaminants, ready for filtration\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitplasmaheater.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §623§7x§615§7x§615§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   669x §r§7Reinforced Sterile Water Plant Casing\n§6   54x §r§7Heat-Resistant Trinium Plated Casing\n§6   64x §r§7Any Tinted Industrial Glass\n§6   40x §r§7Superconductor Base ZPM Frame Box\n§6   8x §r§7Any Neonite\n§6   9x §r§7Superconducting Coil Block\n§f   Input Hatch (Water): §7§61+\n§f   Output Hatch: §7§61\n§f   Input Hatch (Coolant): §7§61\n§f   Input Hatch (Plasma): §7§61\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunituvtreatment.name=고출력 레이저 정화 장치
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunituvtreatment.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePurification Unit§r\n§b§lWater Tier: §f6§r\nMust be linked to a Purification Plant using a data stick to work\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nDuring operation, swap the lens in the §fLens Housing\nThe multiblock will output a signal through the §fLens Indicator Hatch\nwhen the current lens must be swapped\nLens swaps will be requested in random intervals of §c3 to 15s\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nSuccess chance is boosted by §c10.0% §7for each successful swap performed.\nRemoving a lens too early will fail the recipe\nFind the order of lenses in the recipe in NEI,\nor use a portable scanner to view the currently requested lens\nThe recipe always starts at the Orundum Lens\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§b§oThe sixth step of water purification involves identifying any remaining negatively charged ions within\n§b§othe water which may cause electrical faults in future wafer manufacturing. Bombarding the water with varying\n§b§owavelengths of photon beams will impart energy into outer-shell electrons, causing them to detach from the\n§b§oatoms themselves and pass through the walls of the tank, ensuring the water is perfectly electrically polar.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunituvtreatment.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §613§7x§69§7x§69§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   147x§7 - §6155x §r§7Naquadria-Reinforced Water Plant Casing\n§6   144x §r§7Electron-Permeable Neutronium Coated Glass\n§6   29x §r§7High Energy Ultraviolet Emitter Casing\n§6   56x §r§7Stellar Alloy Frame Box\n§f   Input Hatch, Output Hatch: §7§61+\n§f   Lens Housing: §7§61\n§f   Lens Indicator: §7§61\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
