    S:gt.blockmachines.neutronactivator.name=중성자 활성화기
    S:gt.blockmachines.neutronactivator.tooltip=Machine Type: §eNeutron Activator, NA§r\nSuperluminal-velocity Motion.\nThe minimum height of the Speeding Pipe Casing is 4\nPer extra Speeding Pipe Casing will give time discount\nBut it will reduce the Neutron Accelerator efficiency\nYou need to input energy to the Neutron Accelerator to get it running\nIt will output correct products with Specific Neutron Kinetic Energy\nOtherwise it will output trash\nThe Neutron Kinetic Energy will decrease 72KeV/s when no Neutron Accelerator is running\nIt will explode when the Neutron Kinetic Energy is over§c 1200MeV§7.\nInputting Graphite/Beryllium dust can reduce 10MeV per dust immediately.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.neutronactivator.tooltip_secondary=   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   7x§7 - §631x §r§7Clean Stainless Steel Machine Casing\n§6   18x §r§7Processor Machine Casing\n§6   16x §r§7Steel Frame Box (minimum)\n§6   4x §r§7Speeding Pipe Casing (minimum)\n§6   32x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (minimum)\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Hint Block Number 1\n§f   Input Bus: §7Hint Block Number 1\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Hint Block Number 2\n§f   Output Bus: §7Hint Block Number 2\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Hint Block Number 2\n§f   Neutron Accelerator: §7Hint Block Number 2\n§f   Neutron Sensor: §7Hint Block Number 2\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.nuclearsaltprocessingplant.controller.tier.single.name=핵용융염 가공 공장
    S:gt.blockmachines.nuclearsaltprocessingplant.controller.tier.single.tooltip=Machine Type: §eReactor Processing Unit, Cold Trap, NSPP§r\n§62§7 Parallels per §fVoltage§7 Tier\n§a250%§7 Speed\n§8100%§7 EU Usage\nProcesses depleted nuclear salts that come from the LFTR\nHandles the recipes of the Reactor Processor Unit and Cold Trap\nOnly Thermally Insulated Casings can be replaced with hatches\nMufflers on top, Energy Hatches on bottom, exactly 2 of each are required\nMaintenance Hatch goes on the back, opposite of the controller block\nInputs go on the left side of the multi, outputs on the right side\n§5500 §7Pollution per second\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.nuclearsaltprocessingplant.controller.tier.single.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63§7x§63§7x§63§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   58x §r§7IV Machine Casing (minimum)\n§6   1x §r§7Thermally Insulated Casing (minimum)\n§f   Input Bus: §7Left Half\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Left Half\n§f   Output Bus: §7Right Half\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Right Half\n§f   Muffler Hatch: §7Top Side, 2 Required\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Bottom Side, 2 Required\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Back Side, Opposite of Controller\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
