    S:gt.blockmachines.synchrotron.name=싱크로트론
    S:gt.blockmachines.synchrotron.tooltip=Machine Type: §eParticle Accelerator§r\nTorus-shaped, uses an electromagnetic field to make beams of charged particles travel in a circle\nElectrically neutral particles are therefore unaffected\nDue to the relativistic Larmor effect, it produces then outputs a photon beam\nThe §9Beam Energy§7, §cBeam Focus§7, and §6Beam Rate§7 are all determined by the formulae in this tooltip\nUse a §bportable scanner §7for info about the input/output of this multiblock\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§b32 kL/s§7 of §bcoolant§7 is required for operation, and §chot coolant§f is returned\nThe input beam must have a §cFocus§7 of at least 25\nThe §cOutput Beam Focus§7 can be improved by using lower temperature coolant\nValid coolants:\n  §bLiquid Nitrogen§7 : §690K\n  §bLiquid Oxygen§7 : §690K\n  §bCoolant§7 : §660K\n  §bSuper Coolant§7 : §61K\nThere are two types of §3Antenna Casings§7, upgrade them to improve the machine\nAll energies in the following formulae must be in keV\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§9Output Beam Energy§7§f = §cIR §f* §2Power Scale Factor\nwhere §cIR §f =  (§eInput Beam Energy§f)^(1.13*(§3Antenna Tier§f)^(4/9))/40,000,000\nand §2Power Scale Factor§f = 1 - 0.15^(§9Total EU/t Provided§f / (30,384 * (§3Antenna Tier§f)^(2.5)))\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§cOutput Beam Focus§7§fdepends on the relation between §eInput Beam Focus§f and §3Machine Focus§f\n§fwhere §aMachine Focus§f = max(min(1.5^(12 - §6Coolant Temperature§f/40), 90), 10)\nIf §eInput Beam Focus§f > §3Machine Focus§f, §cOutput Beam Focus§7§f = (§eInput Beam Focus§f + §aMachine Focus§f)/2.5\nIf §eInput Beam Focus§f <= §3Machine Focus§f, §cOutput Beam Focus§7§f = §eInput Beam Focus§f * §aMachine Focus§f/100\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§6Output Beam Rate§7§f = floor(2.5^(§3Antenna Tier§f) * sqrt(§9Total EU/t Provided)§f * §eInput Beam Rate§f/15,000)\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.synchrotron.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §636§7x§67§7x§634§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   676x §r§7Shielded Accelerator Casing\n§6   90x §r§7Superdense Casting Basin Casing\n§6   64x §r§7Niobium Cavity Machine Casing\n§6   28x §r§7Coolant Delivery Casing\n§6   16x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (LuV+)\n§6   4x §r§7Antenna Casing (must match) (tiered)\n§f   Beamline Input Hatch: §7Hint block with number 1\n§f   Beamline Output Hatch: §7Hint block with number 2\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Hint block with number 3\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Hint block with number 4\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Hint block with number 5\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Hint block with number 6\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   Uses sub channel §6antenna§r§7 for §6Antenna Casing Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.target_chamber.name=표적 챔버
    S:gt.blockmachines.target_chamber.tooltip=Machine Type: §eCollision Chamber§r\nEngraves Wafers with §dParticle Beams§7 and §aMasks§7\nUse a §bportable scanner §7for info about the input/output of this multiblock\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§aMasks§7 have limited durability, degrading by 1 with each engraving\nNEI shows the required §dparticle type§7, minimum §bEU/t\nminimum §cBeam Focus§7, minimum §6Beam Rate§7(Amount), and required §9Beam Energy Range\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nThe incoming §dBeam§7 must be within the required §9Energy Range§7, be the correct §dparticle type\nand have sufficient §cFocus§7 and §6Rate\n§fProcessing Time§7 is determined solely by the §eBeam Rate§7\n§fProcessing Time = 5 seconds * §6Minimum Required Rate§f / §eInput Beam Rate§7\nCan process up to the durability of all §aMask's§7 in the Focus Input Bus of one type per game tick\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.target_chamber.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§65§7x§66§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   29x §r§7Grate Machine Casing\n§6   28x §r§7Shielded Accelerator Casing\n§6   16x §r§7Any Tiered Glass\n§6   34x §r§7Shielded Accelerator Glass\n§6   4x §r§7Target Receptacle\n§6   4x §r§7Focus Manipulator\n§6   1x §r§7Focus Holder\n§6   1x §r§7Target Holder\n§f   Focus Input Bus: §7Hint block with number 1\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Hint block with number 2\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Hint block with number 2\n§f   Input Bus: §7Hint block with number 3\n§f   Output Bus: §7Hint block with number 4\n§f   Beamline Input Hatch: §7Hint block with number 5\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
